    "summary": "This process involves stilbene ester synthesis via nucleophilic addition-elimination mechanism using sodium methoxide as the base in methanol solvent. The reaction was conducted in a T-shaped borosilicate glass microreactor with electroosmotic flow (EOF) pumping at a flow rate of 0.4 mL/min and 20-minute residence time. The flow process achieved a 70% yield compared to 60% in batch under similar conditions (20-minute reaction time in methanol). The microreactor setup provided improved mixing and heat transfer compared to batch processing, resulting in a 10 percentage point yield improvement. The single-phase liquid operation in the microreactor enabled better control over reaction conditions and more efficient mass transfer.",
